The article is a transcript of a press briefing by Press Secretary Jay Carney, Deputy National Security Advisor for Strategic Communications Ben Rhodes, and USAID Administrator Raj Shah. The briefing took place at the King Fahd Palace Hotel in Dakar, Senegal. The officials discussed President Obama's trip to Africa and previewed some of the events and topics that would be covered during the trip. They highlighted the focus on increasing trade and investment in Africa, strengthening democratic institutions, investing in young people, and renewing US engagement in the region. They also discussed specific events and initiatives related to food security, young people, US partnership with Africa, and increasing trade and investment. The officials also addressed questions about Edward Snowden, corruption in Africa, and the health of Nelson Mandela.